        "description": "For immutable buffers (i.e. most of them), the {{mutable_data_}} member is uninitialized. If the user calls {{mutable_data()}} by mistake on such a buffer, they will get a bogus pointer back.\r\n\r\nThis is exacerbated by the Tensor API whose const and non-const {{raw_data()}} methods return different things...\r\n\r\n(also an idea: add a DCHECK for mutability before returning from {{mutable_data()}}?)",
